{"talk":{"id":1976,"name":"Jeremy Kasdin: The flower-shaped starshade that might help us detect Earth-like planets","description":"Astronomers believe that every star in the galaxy has a planet, one fifth of which might harbor life. Only we haven't seen any of them -- yet. Jeremy Kasdin and his team are looking to change that with the design and engineering of an extraordinary piece of equipment: a flower petal-shaped \"starshade\" positioned 50,000 km from a telescope to enable imaging of planets about distant stars. It is, he says, the \"coolest possible science.\"","slug":"jeremy_kasdin_the_flower_shaped_starshade_that_might_help_us_detect_earth_like_planets","recorded_at":"2014-03-19 00:00:00","published_at":"2014-04-17 15:01:01","updated_at":"2020-09-28 21:46:29","viewed_count":1378260,"emailed_count":0,"event":{"id":256,"name":"TED2014"},"images":[{"image":{"size":"113x85","url":"https:\/\/pe.tedcdn.com\/images\/ted\/3e31ca794b75d058ffd2d7bce4c775670509a515_113x85.jpg"}},{"image":{"size":"240x180","url":"https:\/\/pe.tedcdn.com\/images\/ted\/3e31ca794b75d058ffd2d7bce4c775670509a515_240x180.jpg"}},{"image":{"size":"615x461","url":"https:\/\/pe.tedcdn.com\/images\/ted\/3e31ca794b75d058ffd2d7bce4c775670509a515_615x461.jpg"}},{"image":{"size":"1600x1200","url":"https:\/\/pe.tedcdn.com\/images\/ted\/3e31ca794b75d058ffd2d7bce4c775670509a515_1600x1200.jpg"}}],"image_16x9":false,"media":{"internal":{"64k":{"uri":"https:\/\/download.ted.com\/talks\/JeremyKasdin_2014-64k.mp4?apikey=c692baa7dafbf74e4fbde1ac88b44cafc96cfe7a","filesize_bytes":3272309,"mime_type":"video\/mp4"},"180k":{"uri":"https:\/\/download.ted.com\/talks\/JeremyKasdin_2014-180k.mp4?apikey=c692baa7dafbf74e4fbde1ac88b44cafc96cfe7a","filesize_bytes":9008519,"mime_type":"video\/mp4"},"320k":{"uri":"https:\/\/download.ted.com\/talks\/JeremyKasdin_2014-320k.mp4?apikey=c692baa7dafbf74e4fbde1ac88b44cafc96cfe7a","filesize_bytes":15995736,"mime_type":"video\/mp4"},"450k":{"uri":"https:\/\/download.ted.com\/talks\